    "created_at": "2017-06-29T17:36:38Z",
    "updated_at": "2017-06-29T17:40:06Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "This one will be tough to fix.\r\nAnything that invokes attack move gets its activity queue reset.\r\nSee Hunt.cs for example. In Hunt it invokes attack move.\r\nThen In attackbase.cs, in InnterTick,\r\n\r\npublic void AttackTarget(Target target, bool queued, bool allowMove, bool forceAttack = false) function is called as a non-queued move so\r\n\r\n\t\tif (!queued)\r\n\t\t\tself.CancelActivity();\r\n\r\nIt cancels everything. It should only cancel necessary parts of the activity graph.\r\nThis one is blocking multi-waypoint rally point system too. (although it seems no one tried to implement it yet)"
  },
