    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Sorry for sounding harsh, but this all isn't exactly new, and I explained the problems related to attack-move and activities quite a few times already.  The fact is, `AttackMove` only ever works correctly when it is invoked by a player. It *just will not work as expected* when you just call the activity, be it in C# code or in Lua scripts, because it doesn't do enough. I explained why with these [two](https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/issues/7454#issuecomment-73757364) [comments](https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/issues/7454#issuecomment-107056625). https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/compare/bleed...obrakmann:activities-pt3 will fix this eventually.\r\n\r\nAlso, again, calling `self.CancelActivity()` *anywhere* besides the code that handles the `Stop` command (plus a handful of exceptions, such as the Lua method with the same name or evaluating non-queued orders), is a bug. Hence [this comment](https://github.com/OpenRA/OpenRA/blob/bleed/OpenRA.Game/Activities/Activity.cs#L40).\r\n\r\nAnd this is still a duplicate of #7454."
